  <name>Digger</name>
  <summary>DNS lookup tool with an intuitive GTK interface</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Digger is a modern DNS lookup tool built with GTK4 and libadwaita that provides 
      an intuitive interface for performing DNS queries and exploring DNS records.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Support for all major DNS record types (A, AAAA, MX, CNAME, NS, TXT, SOA, SRV, PTR)</li>
      <li>Advanced DNS options including reverse lookups, trace queries, and custom DNS servers</li>
      <li>Query history with search and filtering capabilities</li>
      <li>One-click copying of DNS record values to clipboard</li>
      <li>Modern adaptive interface that works well on desktop and mobile</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcuts for improved productivity</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
  <screenshots>
    <screenshot type="default">
      <image>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tobagin/digger-vala/main/screenshots/main-window.png</image>
      <caption>Main application window showing DNS lookup interface</caption>
    </screenshot>
  </screenshots>
  
  <url type="homepage">https://github.com/tobagin/digger-vala</url>
  <url type="bugtracker">https://github.com/tobagin/digger-vala/issues</url>
  
  <developer_name>tobagin</developer_name>
  <update_contact>tobagin@example.com</update_contact>
  
  <provides>
    <binary>digger-vala</binary>
  </provides>
  
